================================================================================
PART 5: Single-shift entries analysis
================================================================================

If every nonzero entry of B has exactly ONE contributing (sign, shift) pair,
then B_k[i,j] = sign * omega^{k*shift} = omega^{k*shift} * B_0[i,j]
which is exactly the diagonal gauge with d[i,j] depending only on shift.

  Degree m=1: 0 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

  Degree m=2: 3 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

  Degree m=3: 2 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

  Degree m=4: 5 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

  Degree m=5: 10 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

  Degree m=6: 6 single-shift entries, 0 multi-shift entries

================================================================================
PART 6: Vertex-sum gauge conjecture
================================================================================

Conjecture: B_k = D_k^row * B_0 * D_k^col
where D_k^row[i,i] = omega^{k * f(path_i)}
and D_k^col[j,j] = omega^{k * g(path_j)}
for some functions f, g of the path.

Natural candidates for f, g:
  (a) sum of vertices mod n
  (b) sum of interior vertices mod n
  (c) last vertex mod n
  (d) first + last vertex mod n

